@node 1 "About"

 Telephone Book V 3.4  By Stuart Kelly  Copyright 1997 ｩ

 Written in C.

 I use @{" DCC " link dcc } to compile my programs.
 
 Telephone Book only works with Workbench 2.0 and above.
 
 If you have any comments or suggestions, write a letter to me at the
 following @{" Address " link address}.  I know have an email address
 so you can also send comment/suuggestion to this @{" email address " link address}

 TB3.4 is FREEWARE

 Please Note that I think FREEWARE is not PD - You can`t do what you want
 with it, there are some Copyrights to be obey.  If this is wrong please
 contact me.

 Since TB3.4 is FREEWARE you do not have to send anything to me, but I
 would appreciate anything you want to send me.  EG email message, postcard,
 etc...

 @{" About Me    " link stu}
 @{" Suggestions " link suggest}
 @{" Thank You   " link thanks}
 @{" Contents    " link Main}

@ENDNODE

@node install "Install? How?

 To install double click on the install.TB icon.

 TB3.4 now uses Commodore's @{fg shine}installer@{fg text} program because it is a very easy to
 use and time to write a script.

 To install select where you want to install TB and press @{fg shine}Proceed@{fg text}.

 Note:- TB3.4 will not create a drawer, so you will have to create one.

 If you need any help just press the @{fg shine}Help@{fg text} buttons.

 @{" Commodore " link cac}
 @{" Contents  " link Main}

@ENDNODE

