@node cwin "Close Window"

 Close the File window.  Same as pressing the Close Gadget.
 
 @{" File Menus " link fmenu}
 
@endnode 

@node n8 "Edit"

 Edit lets you edit a TB file in memory if there is no file in memory then
 the Edit button is disabled.

 When the window appers you can edit the info.
 
 Press OK to update the file.
 Press Cancel to use the old data.

 @{" New Functions " link new}
 @{" File          " link 4}

@endnode

@node n7 "Export"

 This will Export any TB3.4 file in memory.  The file will be save as a
 text file which can be changed using ED.

 @{" File " link 4}

@ENDNODE

@node n1 "Load"

 Load a file.  When the file requester appers select the file you wish
 to load and press Load.  Press Cancel if you don`t wish to load.

 @{" File " link 4}

@ENDNODE

@node n2 "Save"

 Save a file.  When the file requester appers select the place you wish to
 save the file, and a name for the file in the requester if it is wrong.
 Then press Save on the requester.  Press Cancel if you don`t wish to save.

 NOTE:- The name for the file will be the current name & surname.
        Eg:- 'Stuart-Kelly' ( with out the ' marks ).
 
 The file will be saved with a project icon, with the default tool set to
 TB3.4.

 NOTE:- If you double click on the icon of the file you saved and it is in
        the same directory as TB3.4.  TB3.4 will run.  But you will still
        have to load the file using @{" Load " link n1} in the file window.

 @{" File " link 4}

@ENDNODE

@node n3 "Delete"

 Delete a file.

 A file requester will apper.  Select a file to delete and press Delete! to
 delete the file.  Pressing Cancel will not delete any files.

 NOTE: Delete will not accept wild cards ( eg #? ).
 
 @{" File " link 4}

@ENDNODE

@node n4 "New"

 When you press 'New' then:-

 1. A window will apper called New File.
 2. Enter your data.
 3. Press OK or Cancel.

 What data is needed:-
 
 Telephone Number         -  eg 123456
 Name                     -  eg Stuart 
 Surname                  -  eg Kelly
 Door Number              -  eg 8
 First Part Of Road Name  -  eg Squires  - Road A
 Second Part Of Road Name -  eg Wood     - Road B
 Third Part of Road Name  -  eg          - Road C
 Area                     -  eg Fulwood
 Town / City              -  eg Preston
 Post Code                -  eg PR2 9QA
 DCode                    -  eg 01772
 EMail                    -  eg None

 NOTE: If your address has only 2 parts to its road name eg 'Squires Wood'
       then leave the third part of the road name empty.

 @{" File                " link 4}
 @{" New Functions       " link new}

@ENDNODE

@node n5 "Print"

 Print a file.  When the requester appers, read the message.

 The Buttons:-

 Press Cancel to Quit ( Don`t Print ).
 Press Print to Print.

 Don`t Print if your printer is off or is not connected.  This may
 cause TB3.4 to crash.

 @{" TBPrint V 1.05 " link TBPrint}

 @{" File " link 4}

@ENDNODE

@node TBPrint "TBPrint V 1.05"

 NOTE TBPrint needs @{" CLITB " link bugs}.

 Don`t Print without the printer on or TBPrint will crash!
 
 TBPrint is an extra utility I made.  It loads TB3.1 and above files, and
 displays all the data in the file.  TBPrint as 2 windows each with buttons.

 Window 1 (TBPrint) :- Shows the file loaded and has a button in the top
                       right corner saying @{fg shine}Print As Text@{fg text}.  This lets you
                       save the file as a text file.  When you press this
                       button it displays a file requester asking you where
                       to save the file.  @{fg shine}Save@{fg text} saves the file, @{fg shine}Cancel@{fg text} does
                       not save the file.
                       Also Window 1 has a button called C&RL. If you press
                       this it will Clear the list & Load the file again.

 Keys to press when Window 1 is active:

 @{fg shine}a@{fg text} - Press this an a file requester will apper.
                          This will let you pick an Arexx script to run.
                          Select a scrpit to run and press OK, or press
                          Cancel.

 @{fg shine}q@{fg text} - Press this to Quit.

 --------------------------------------------------------------------------

 Window 2 (Print) :- This has 3 Buttons:- 1. Print All - Prints all of the
                                                         file.
                                          2. Print Label - Prints the file
                                                           as an address
                                                           label. has the
                                                           PostCode.
                                          3. Help - Loads help.

 --------------------------------------------------------------------------

 To Install TBPrint:- 1. Open Shell.
                      2. Type `copy df0:TBPrint to C:'

 To Use: C:TBPrint <filename>      The filename is the TB3.1 and above file
                                 you wish to load.

 Now you can load TB3.4 files without using this disk.

 TBPrint can also be used from Arexx.

 @{" TBPrint Arexx Commands " link tbp-a}
 @{" New Functions          " link new}
 @{" Go Back                " link n5}

@ENDNODE

@node tbp-a "TBPrint Arexx Commands"

 TBPrint V 1.05 now has Arexx commands like EDel.

 TBPrint's Arexx Port Name: @{fg shine}TBPRINT.1@{fg text}

 Commands:-

 @{fg shine}TEST            @{fg text} - Send a test message to TBPrint.
 @{fg shine}SETF <filename> @{fg text} - Set the current filename to <filename>.
 @{fg shine}CLR             @{fg text} - Clear and Load current filename.
 @{fg shine}PTEXT <filename>@{fg text} - Print as Text to <filename>.
 @{fg shine}PLABEL          @{fg text} - Print as Label.
 @{fg shine}PALL            @{fg text} - Print All.
 @{fg shine}QUIT            @{fg text} - Make TBPrint Quit.
 @{fg shine}HELP            @{fg text} - Show this guide.
 @{fg shine}SMAIL           @{fg text} - Show EMail Address.


 Example Script :-

 @{fg shine}/* Print '/Numbers/Example.TB' as a label.  Using TBPrint */
 ADDRESS 'TBPRINT.1'
 'SETF /Numbers/Example.TB'
 'CLR'
 'PLABEL'
 'QUIT'@{fg text}
 
 @{" TBPrint  " link TBPrint}
 @{" Contents " link main}

@endnode 

@node n6 "Display"

 This displays the current file.  Close the window to continue.

 It Looks like this:-
