@node TBT "TBTools"

 TBTools is a program that lets you access some of the programs that come
 with TB3.4  TBTools has the following buttons:-

 TB3.4      - Run Telephone Book V 3.4
 @{" TBView  " link TBV} - Run TBView.
 Help       - View this guide (Uses Multiview).
 @{" Menu 3  " link Menu3} - Run Menu 3.
 QUIT       - Quit TBTools.
 About      - About TBTools.
 @{" Colours " link colour} - Edit colours.
 EDel       - Deletes files.

 @{" TBTools Menus " link TBM}

 @{" Press me ", link "MODS/TBT.IFF/MAIN"} to view the window.
 
 To run TBTools double click on the TBTools icon in the TBTools drawer.

 Note: TBTools may be replaced by @{" ATools " link atool} in the final version of TB3.4.
 
 @{" TBExtras      " link TBE}
 @{" New Functions " link new}

@endnode

@node TBV "TBView"

 Name of program:- TBView.
 Where is it?   :- TBTools/TBView.
 What is it for?:- To view TB3.4 files with out using TB3.4.

 TBView lets you view TB3.4 files with out using TB3.4 in anyway.

 To use it you can use @{" TBTools " link TBT} which has a file requester or
 you can use it from shell:-

 'TBView [filename]'

 The filename must be a TB file or the program may not work.

 @{" TBExtras      " link TBE}
 @{" New Functions " link new}
  
@endnode

@node TBM "TBTools Menus"

 TBTools                           Progs
    |                                |
   About - About TBTools.           TB3.4   - Run TB3.4.
   Help  - View This Guide.        @{" TBView  " link TBV }
                                   @{" Menu 3  " link Menu3}
   ~~~~~~~                         @{" Colours " link colour}
   Quit  - Quit TBTools.           @{" RunIt   " link RI}

 @{" TBTools " link TBT}

@endnode

@node RI "RunIt"

 RunIt lets you run any program.

 Usage:- 1. Click in the string gadget.
         2. Enter the path and name of the program you want to run. Eg:-
            'Multiview'.
         3. Press Run.

 Note:- If you change the window size the gadgets will also change size.
        This program uses Intuition to tell when it has to change it's
        gadgets size.  The gadgets are not BOOPSI gadgets, the are Gadtools
        gadgets.

 @{" TBTools Menus " link TBM}

@endnode

@node prefs "Prefs"

 These are programs that let you decide how TB3.4 works.

 @{" Help Prefs    " link hp}
 @{" Edit Colours  " link colour}
 @{" EDC           " link 9}
 @{" New Functions " link new}

 @{" Contents   " link main}
 
@endnode

@node hp "Help Prefs"

 This program lets you choose which program you want to view this guide
 with.  All TB programs can then read the config file and view this guide
 using the program you picked.

 To run the program double click on the HelpPrefs icon in the Prefs drawer.

 A window will apper with 4 Gadgets, 3 Button Gadgets and 1 String Gadget.

 @{fg shine}The String Gadget@{fg text} - next to the Find button lets you type in a program to
                     use.  The full path and name must be given eg
                     'SYS:Utilities/Multiview'.

 @{fg shine}The Find Button@{fg text} - makes the job of selecting a program easier.  When you
                   press this button a file requester will apper asking you
                   to select a program to use.  Press the Use button and the
                   program you selected will apper in the string gadget.
                   Press Cancel and the string gadget will not be affected.

 @{fg shine}The Save Button@{fg text} - Press this and the program you selected will be used by
                   TB3.4 to view this guide ( @{" Help " link 8} ).  This
                   will save the prefs to ENV: and ENVARC:

 @{fg shine}The Use Button@{fg text} - Press thts and the program you selected will be saved to
                  ENV: only.

 @{fg shine}The Cancel Button@{fg text} - Press this and the program used by TB3.4 will not
                     change.

 Note: That if you press Use it will only save the prefs to ram:env/  If you
       want to save the prefs forever use the Save button.  This saves the
       prefs to ram:env/ and envarc: - On your Workbench disk.

 @{" Contents " link main}

@endnode

@node atool "What's ATools"

 So you what to know what ATools is do you?

 Well ATools is a new program I've be working on which has a custom button
 images and functions.  To see a preview of ATools press @{" me " link "MODS/AT.IFF/MAIN"}

 At the moment I've not finished ATools V 1.01 and not even tested it
 for bugs!

 A demo version may be included with TB3.4.  To find out more write/email
 me at my @{" address " link address}.
 
 @{" TBTools " link TBT}

@endnode 

